Attention Dear Parents and Seniors:

PLEASE READ THIS MESSAGE CAREFULLY

Graduation rehearsal will begin tomorrow at 10:30 a.m. and will run until 1 p.m. However, certification of graduates and the distribution of tickets, and cap and gowns is POSTPONED UNTIL MONDAY 8:30 A.M. You must be in attendance for Friday's rehearsal in order to receive your materials on Monday morning.

Friday will be a FULL rehearsal (including sample speeches and singing). NO CAP AND GOWNS, TICKETS WILL BE GIVEN OUT TOMORROW. AND IF YOU OWE SENIOR DUES, YOU WILL BE ABLE TO PAY THAT TOMORROW. YOU WILL NOT RECEIVE YOUR CAMP AND GOWN UNLESS YOUR DUES ARE PAID IN FULL.

Monday will include certification, cap and gown as well as ticket distribution. YOU MUST PICK ALL MATERIALS BETWEEN 8:30- 1O A.M. MONDAY. No cap and gowns will be given out after 10 a.m. as FINAL preparations for graduation need to be made.

THANK YOU
